@database "mfkey"
@author Alfonso Ranieri

@Node "Main" "mfkey"

    @{u}@{b}mfkey@{ub}@{uu}
    Written by Alfonso Ranieri


    @{" Author " LINK "Author"} @{" WRID " LINK "WRID"} @{" Changes " LINK "Changes"}


    @{fg fill}mfkey@{fg text} is a little tool to associate functions to keys.

    @{fg fill}mfkey@{fg text} template and tooltypes are:

    @{fg shine}CX_PRIORITY/K/N,CX_POPKEY/K,CX_POPUP/S,USECXPARSE@{fg text}

    - @{fg shine}CX_PRIORITY@{fg text}
      the priority of the commodity; default 0

    - @{fg shine}CX_POPKEY@{fg text}
      a key to popup mfkey GUI; default none; suggested "control alt f"

    - @{fg shine}CX_POPUP/S@{fg text}
      if supplied, the gui is shown

    - @{fg shine}USECXPARSE/S@{fg text}
      if supplied, the original commodities.library/ParseIX() function
      is used, otherwise an internal one takes place in order to parse
      F10, F11 and F12 (that are not parsed as MorphOS <=1.5)


    You may install @{fg fill}mfkey@{fg text} anywhere and run it from WBStartup
    or add the line

    @{fg shine}run >NIL: <NIL: mfkey@{fg text}

    to your user-startup.


    Of course, you must setup @{fg fill}mfkey@{fg text}, adding keys to it.

    Some note:

    @{fg shine}CLI@{fg text} - commands are run as you typed them in a shell; you
    get no input and no output; you may defined a path that is
    is used as the current dir; you may define both PPC and
    68K stack. Note that "Multiview file" doesn't work, use
    "Sys:Utilities/Multiview file" instead.

    @{fg shine}WB@{fg text} - wb commands are run as you double clicked on their
    icons; you may define a path that is used as the root dir;
    you may defined a stack that is used as 68k stack; note
    that PPC stack is set as the double of 68K stack in
    wbstart.library Ambient emulation.

    @{fg shine}RX@{fg text} - ARexx macros are started sending a command to AREXX
    port (not to REXX !); you get no input and no output.

    If @{fg shine}Swallow@{fg text} is selected, the key event is not propagated.

    If you need more complex stuff, just create a script file
    (cmd.bat) and run it as a CLI command as "execute cmd.bat".

    @{fg fill}mfkey@{fg text} uses Hotkeystring.mcc if it finds it. MUI4
    Hotkeyadjust.mui is not usable because of it doesn't
    notify MUIA_String_Contents.

    If ENV:MUI/UseNList is found and set to not 0, @{fg fill}mfkey@{fg text} uses
    NList classes instead of List ones.

@EndNode

